verbose_text: Doxorubicin is reduced by nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide phosphate-oxidase (NADPH oxidase) to a semi-quinone free radical, which in turn interacts with oxygen to form superoxide, hydroxyl and peroxynitrite free radicals.
